@node "What's MIDIpreter ?" "What's MIDIpreter ?"

@{b}@{fg shine} What's MIDIpreter ?@{u}@{fg text}

@{ub}@{uu}
MIDIpreter is not what I would call an extremly usefully
MIDI-program, but it's rather funny or at least nice-looking.

MIDIpreter was basically written to test a procedure analysing a
MIDI-Input-Stream. But after the procedure seemed to work I
thought of how it would look alike if the program reacts to notes
coming in with different graphical outputs; make the the music
almost visible..

This second release includes @{"12álittleámodules" link "Modules" 0} interpreting
incoming MIDI-notes  -  check it out !
@endnode

@node "Modules" "Modules"

@{b}@{fg shine}  Included Modules@{ub}@{fg text}


This release includes ten modules reacting to incoming notes, most
of them influenced by velocity and Note value. Here's a short
description of what they do..

@{b}@{i}
 À Dot Matrix@{ub}@{ui}

      A dot matrix is printed at random screen positions.
      Great velocity causes bigger matrix.


@{b}@{i} À Vert Lines@{ub}@{ui}

      Each note is represented by a vertical line.
      Color/length depends on velocity.


@{b}@{i} À Hori Lines@{ub}@{ui}

      Each note is represented by a horizontal line
      Color/length depends on velocity.


@{b}@{i} À Roto Lines@{ub}@{ui}

      Each note is represented by a rotated line,
      Velocity controlls degree of rotation@{b}@{i}


@{b}@{i} À Stars@{ub}@{ui}

      Each note causes a star.
      Velocity sets size/color.


@{b}@{i} À Rubber band@{ub}@{ui}

      Imagine a rubber band tack to every corner and
      a 'virtual' note in the middle of your screen..


@{b}@{i} À Bars@{ub}@{ui}

      Almost like <Hori Lines> but using rectangles


@{b}@{i} À Keys@{ub}@{ui}

      Something like a keyboard is printed for each note
      I have to improve this dumb module.. :-7
                                              .. any ideas ?


@{b}@{i} À Equalizer@{ub}@{ui}

      Each note is represented by an equalizer-like
      levelmeter, nothing great at all..


@{b}@{i} À PrintNotes@{ub}@{ui}

      Prints out Tone-Nr. of each note
      Velocity sets Y-Coord.


@{b}@{i} À PrintNotes 2.0@{ub}@{ui}

      Displays note+octave, beneath a small pyramid is drawn..
      Velocity sets Y-Coord.




These modules aren't really masterpieces of graphical programming,
they're absolutely primitive and most of them mind-boggingly
ugly.

But compared to the first release they're slightly enhanced and no
one should be tortured with this early stuff.

So watch out for @{"futureáimprovements" link "The future" 0}..
@endnode

