@node "Requirements" "Requirements"

@{b}@{fg shine}  Requirements@{ub}@{fg text}


MIDIpreter requires OS2.1.

It could even be usefully to connect a MIDI-Interface to your
serial device, with a MIDI-Keyboard on the <IN>-Side and probably
dozens of synthesizers connected to the <OUT> - Side.

All graphicboards should work just fine with MIDIpreter.
@endnode

@node "How to use MIDIpreter" "How to use MIDIpreter"

@{b}@{fg shine}  How to use MIDIpreter@{ub}@{fg text}


To start MIDIpreter, just double-click the icon or type the name
via the CLI.

MIDIpreter opens a Screenmode-Requester to let you choose your
preferred resolution. By the way, graphicsboards can be used
without any problem, too.


MIDI-THRU will be enabled after closing the menu. To re-open the
window, you can use <Program Change>, <Pitch Bend> or <Volume>
messages, selecting using the <This window> gadget.

To adjust the palette, just click <Palette> and an almost
self-explaining palette-editor will appear.
@endnode

@node "The future" "The future"

@{b}@{fg shine}  The future..@{ub}@{fg text}


I've got already some nice ideas how to improve MIDIpreter an I
hope that one day, MIDIpreter will become more like an interactive
and fully configurable AGA-Demo than this crapped graphic
primitives, to let you create your personal impressive music-video
.. so hold on !!


In the meantime the next releases may include the following..

In connection with the midi.library which is used by, e.g.,
MIDI-Play, the MIDI-Out-Stream of MIDIPlay could be used to
control MIDIpreter or a Standard-MIDI-File-Player will be included
in MIDIpreter..


Much more really attractive modules like bouncing balls, bubbles,
vector-objects, texture-mapping, complex geometric figures ...


A Module-Editor for each module allowing several modules to be
used at the same time, e.g. one for each channel and to make
modules become much more configurable.


If there are enough people interested in such a program, If I find
enough time and energy to realize it, If YOU@{ub}@{ui} send @{"me" link "Author" 0} your ideas,
then there'll probably a new version of MIDIpreter coming to
aminet soon

                                      .@{b}@{i}. stay tuned !
@endnode

